SecretData.description:
The information about the key-value pairs of the Secret. This parameter is required. The following formats are supported:

{"Data":"{"k1":"v1", "k2":"v2"}"}

k specifies a key and v specifies a value. For more information, see [Manage a Kubernetes Secret](~~463383~~).

schema.description:
The key-value pairs of the ConfigMap in the JSON format. Format:

{"Data":"{"k1":"v1", "k2":"v2"}"}

k specifies a key and v specifies a value. For more information, see [Manage a Kubernetes ConfigMap](~~171326~~).

Data.description:
The key-value pairs of the ConfigMap. Format:

{"k1":"v1", "k2":"v2"}

k specifies a key and v specifies a value. For more information, see [Manage a Kubernetes ConfigMap](~~171326~~).

The data of ConfigMap key-value pairs. Format:

{"k1":"v1", "k2":"v2"}

k specifies a key and v specifies a value. For more information, see [Manage and use configurations](~~171326~~).

